name: library_source
definition: The type of study, either genomic, metagenomic, transcriptomic, metatranscriptomic, viral RNA, synthetic or other.

name: library_layout
definition: Type of library layout for sequencing: either paired end or single end

name: insert_size
definition: The number of bases per read sequenced

name: collection_date
definition: The time of sampling; either as an instance (single point in time) or interval. In case no exact time is available; the date/time can be right truncated i.e. all of these are valid times: 2008-01-23T19:23:10+00:00; 2008-01-23T19:23:10; 2008-01-23; 2008-01; 2008; Except: 2008-01; 2008 all are ISO8601 compliant

name: env_biome
definition: Biomes are defined based on factors such as plant structures; leaf types; plant spacing; and other factors like climate. Biome should be treated as the descriptor of the broad ecological context of a sample. Examples include: desert; taiga; deciduous woodland; or coral reef. EnvO (v 2013-06-14) terms can be found via the link: www.environmentontology.org/Browse-EnvO

name: env_feature
definition: Environmental feature level includes geographic environmental features. Compared to biome; feature is a descriptor of the more local environment. Examples include: harbor; cliff; or lake. EnvO (v 2013-06-14) terms can be found via the link: www.environmentontology.org/Browse-EnvO

name: env_material
definition: The environmental material level refers to the material that was displaced by the sample; or material in which a sample was embedded; prior to the sampling event. Environmental material terms are generally mass nouns. Examples include: air; soil; or water. EnvO (v 2013-06-14) terms can be found via the link: www.environmentontology.org/Browse-EnvO

name: geo_loc_name
definition: The geographical origin of the sample as defined by the country or sea name followed by specific region name. Country or sea names should be chosen from the INSDC country list (http://insdc.org/country.html); or the GAZ ontology (v 1.512) (http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/GAZ)

name: alt_elev
definition: the vertical distance between Earth's surface above sea level and the sampled position in the air

name: depth
definition: depth is defined as the vertical distance below local surface; e.g. for sediment or soil samples depth is measured from sediment or soil surface; respectivly. Depth can be reported as an interval for subsurface samples

name: lat_lon
definition: The geographical origin of the sample as defined by latitude and longitude. The values should be reported in decimal degrees and in WGS84 system

name: project_name
definition: The geographical origin of the sample as defined by the country or sea name followed by specific region name. Country or sea names should be chosen from the INSDC country list (http://insdc.org/country.html); or the GAZ ontology (v 1.512) (http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/GAZ)

name: experimental_factor
definition: Experimental factors are essentially the variable aspects of an experiment design which can be used to describe an experiment; or set of experiments; in an increasingly detailed manner. This field accepts ontology terms from Experimental Factor Ontology (EFO) and/or Ontology for Biomedical Investigations (OBI). For a browser of EFO (v 2.43) terms; please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/EFO; for a browser of OBI (v 2013-10-25) terms please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/OBI

name: investigation_type
definition: Nucleic Acid Sequence Report is the root element of all MIGS/MIMS compliant reports as standardized by Genomic Standards Consortium. This field is either eukaryote;bacteria;virus;plasmid;organelle; metagenome;mimarks-survey; or mimarks-specimen

name: submitted_to_insdc
definition: Depending on the study (large-scale e.g. done with next generation sequencing technology; or small-scale) sequences have to be submitted to SRA (Sequence Read Archive); DRA (DDBJ Read Archive) or via the classical Webin/Sequin systems to Genbank; ENA and DDBJ. Although this field is mandatory; it is meant as a self-test field; therefore it is not necessary to include this field in contextual data submitted to databases

name: env_package
definition: MIGS/MIMS/MIMARKS extension for reporting of measurements and observations obtained from one or more of the environments where the sample was obtained. All environmental packages listed here are further defined in separate subtables. By giving the name of the environmental package; a selection of fields can be made from the subtables and can be reported

name: sample_name
definition: A unique name (identifier) for a sample

name: decimalLatitude
definition: The geographic latitude (in decimal degrees; using the spatial reference system given in geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a Location. Positive values are north of the Equator; negative values are south of it. Legal values lie between -90 and 90; inclusive.

name: decimalLongitude
definition: The geographic longitude (in decimal degrees; using the spatial reference system given in geodeticDatum) of the geographic center of a Location. Positive values are east of the Greenwich Meridian; negative values are west of it. Legal values lie between -180 and 180; inclusive.

name: eventID
definition: An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

name: parentEventID
definition: An event identifier for the super event which is composed of one or more sub-sampling events. The value must refer to an existing eventID. If the identifier is local it must exist within the given dataset. May be a globally unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

name: rightsHolder
definition: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource

name: bioproject
definition: An assocated INSDC BioProject number.

name: biosample
definition: An assocated INSDC BioSample number.

name: genbank_accession_numbers
definition: An assocated INSDC GenBank accession number.

name: ownerInstitutionCode
definition: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having ownership of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

name: number_of_bases_predicted
definition: The number of bases predicted in a sequenced sample

name: run_type
definition: The type of sequencing run performed. E.g. Illumina MiSeq 250bp paired-end

name: sra_run_number
definition: An assocated INSDC run accession number. (ERR number)

name: INSDC_SampleID
definition: An assocated INSDC sample accession number. (ERS number)

name: sequence_data_repository
definition: the repository name where the sequences are stored and publicly accessible (e.g. ENA; SRA; VAMPS;...)

name: eventRemarks
definition: Comments or notes about the Event.

name: samplingProtocol
definition: The name of; reference to; or description of the method or protocol used during an Event.

name: scientificNameID
definition: An identifier for the set of taxon information (data associated with the Taxon class). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

name: organismQuantity
definition: A number or enumeration value for the quantity of organisms (or microorganism cells).

name: organismQuantityType
definition: The type of quantification system used for the quantity of organisms.

name: collection_time
definition: the exact time a sample was collected in the field

name: forward_primer
definition: the forward primer name or identifier

name: forward_primer_sequence
definition: the forward primer sequence (use capital letters; following the IUPAC code of DNA basepaire notations)

name: reverse_primer
definition: the reverse primer name or identifier

name: reverse_primer_sequence
definition: the reverse primer sequence (use capital letters; following the IUPAC code of DNA basepaire notations)

name: sample_description
definition: a description of the sample as it was taken from the natural environment

name: acceptedNameUsageID
definition: The taxonID of the taxon considered to be the valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) name for this nameUsage. If acceptedNameUsage is given; the scientificName of the nameUsage with taxonID=acceptedNameUsageID needs to be the same as acceptedNameUsage.

name: associatedReferences
definition: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication; bibliographic reference; global unique identifier; URI) of literature associated with the Occurrence.

name: basisOfRecord
definition: The specific nature of the data record - a subtype of the dcterms:type. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Darwin Core Type Vocabulary (http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/type-vocabulary/index.htm).

name: catalogNumber
definition: An identifier (preferably unique) for the record within the data set or collection.

name: class
definition: The full scientific name of the class in which the taxon is classified.

name: family
definition: The full scientific name of the family in which the taxon is classified.

name: footprintWKT
definition: A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the shape (footprint; geometry) that defines the Location. A Location may have both a point-radius representation (see decimalLatitude) and a footprint representation; and they may differ from each other.

name: genus
definition: The full scientific name of the genus in which the taxon is classified.

name: higherClassification
definition: A list (concatenated and separated) of taxa names terminating at the rank immediately superior to the taxon referenced in the taxon record. Recommended best practice is to order the list starting with the highest rank and separating the names for each rank with a semi-colon (";").

name: infraspecificEpithet
definition: The name of the lowest or terminal infraspecific epithet of the scientificName; excluding any rank designation.

name: kingdom
definition: The full scientific name of the kingdom in which the taxon is classified.

name: license
definition: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

name: locality
definition: The specific description of the place. Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography; continent; country; stateProvince; county; municipality; waterBody; island; islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.

name: nameAccordingTo
definition: The reference to the source in which the specific taxon concept circumscription is defined or implied - traditionally signified by the Latin "sensu" or "sec." (from secundum; meaning "according to"). For taxa that result from identifications; a reference to the keys; monographs; experts and other sources should be given.

name: nameAccordingToID
definition: An identifier for the source in which the specific taxon concept circumscription is defined or implied. See nameAccordingTo.

name: occurenceID
definition: An identifier for the Occurrence (as opposed to a particular digital record of the occurrence). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier; construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the occurrenceID globally unique.

name: order
definition: The full scientific name of the order in which the taxon is classified.

name: originalNameUsageID
definition: An identifier for the name usage (documented meaning of the name according to a source) in which the terminal element of the scientificName was originally established under the rules of the associated nomenclaturalCode.

name: otherCatalogNumbers
definition: A list (concatenated and separated) of previous or alternate fully qualified catalog numbers or other human-used identifiers for the same Occurrence; whether in the current or any other data set or collection.

name: parentNameUsageID
definition: An identifier for the name usage (documented meaning of the name according to a source) of the direct; most proximate higher-rank parent taxon (in a classification) of the most specific element of the scientificName.

name: phylum
definition: The full scientific name of the phylum in which the taxon is classified.

name: ResourceRelationship
definition: Resources can be thought of as identifiable records or instances of classes and may include; but need not be limited to dwc:Occurrence; dwc:Organism; dwc:MaterialSample; dwc:Event; dwc:Location; dwc:GeologicalContext; dwc:Identification; or dwc:Taxon.

name: scientificName
definition: The full scientific name; with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of an Identification; this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications; which should instead be supplied in the IdentificationQualifier term.

name: scientificNameAuthorship
definition: The authorship information for the scientificName formatted according to the conventions of the applicable nomenclaturalCode.

name: scientificNameID
definition: An identifier for the nomenclatural (not taxonomic) details of a scientific name.

name: specificEpithet
definition: The name of the first or species epithet of the scientificName.

name: subgenus
definition: The full scientific name of the subgenus in which the taxon is classified. Values should include the genus to avoid homonym confusion.

name: taxonConceptID
definition: An identifier for the taxonomic concept to which the record refers - not for the nomenclatural details of a taxon.

name: taxonRank
definition: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in the scientificName. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

name: vernacularName
definition: A common or vernacular name.

name: alias
definition: An alternative name of a sample (i.e. synonym to original_name)

name: original_name
definition: The original sample name that can be used to identify the material taken in the field.

name: additional_mid
definition: additional multiplex Identifiers (MIDs); that are used to specifically tag unique samples in a sequencing run. Sequence should be reported in uppercase letters

name: bottle
definition: A name; number or identifier for experiment bottles.

name: carbon_14
definition: carbon isotope 14 reading

name: cast
definition: A form or appearance or character that can group different types of organisms orspecies assemblages together

name: filter_size
definition: the mesh size of the filter used to separate an environmental sample into different size-fractions

name: leucine
definition: the concentration of leucine

name: nitrite_plus_nitrate
definition: the amount or concentration of nitrite pluse nitrate (measured together)

name: density
definition: density of sample

name: biotic_relationship
definition: Is it free-living or in a host and if the latter what type of relationship is observed

name: encoded_traits
definition: Should include key traits like antibiotic resistance or xenobiotic degradation phenotypes for plasmids; converting genes for phage

name: estimated_size
definition: The estimated size of the genome prior to sequencing. Of particular importance in the sequencing of (eukaryotic) genome which could remain in draft form for a long or unspecified period.

name: extrachrom_elements
definition: Do plasmids exist of significant phenotypic consequence (e.g. ones that determine virulence or antibiotic resistance). Megaplasmids? Other plasmids (borrelia has 15+ plasmids)

name: health_disease_stat
definition: Health or disease status of specific host at time of collection. This field accepts PATO (v 2013-10-28) terms; for a browser please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/PATO

name: host_spec_range
definition: The NCBI taxonomy identifier of the specific host if it is known

name: isol_growth_condt
definition: Publication reference in the form of pubmed ID (pmid); digital object identifier (doi) or url for isolation and growth condition specifications of the organism/material

name: num_replicons
definition: Reports the number of replicons in a nuclear genome of eukaryotes; in the genome of a bacterium or archaea or the number of segments in a segmented virus. Always applied to the haploid chromosome count of a eukaryote

name: pathogenicity
definition: To what is the entity pathogenic.

name: ploidy
definition: The ploidy level of the genome (e.g. allopolyploid; haploid; diploid; triploid; tetraploid). It has implications for the downstream study of duplicated gene and regions of the genomes (and perhaps for difficulties in assembly). For terms; please select terms listed under class ploidy (PATO:001374) of Phenotypic Quality Ontology (PATO); and for a browser of PATO (v 2013-10-28) please refer to http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/PATO

name: propagation
definition: This field is specific to different taxa. For phages: lytic/lysogenic; for plasmids: incompatibility group (Note: there is the strong opinion to name phage propagation obligately lytic or temperate; therefore we also give this choice

name: ref_biomaterial
definition: primary publication if isolated before genome publication; otherwise; primary genome report

name: rel_to_oxygen
definition: Is this organism an aerobe; anaerobe? Please note that aerobic and anaerobic are valid descriptors for microbial environments

name: samp_collect_device
definition: The method or device employed for collecting the sample

name: samp_mat_process
definition: Any processing applied to the sample during or after retrieving the sample from environment. This field accepts OBI; for a browser of OBI (v 2013-10-25) terms please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/OBI

name: samp_size
definition: Amount or size of sample (volume; mass or area) that was collected

name: source_mat_id
definition: A unique identifier assigned to a material sample (as defined by http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/materialSampleID; and as opposed to a particular digital record of a material sample) used for extracting nucleic acids; and subsequent sequencing. The identifier can refer either to the original material collected or to any derived sub-samples. The INSDC qualifiers /specimen_voucher; /bio_material; or /culture_collection may or may not share the same value as the source_mat_id field. For instance; the /specimen_voucher qualifier and source_mat_id may both contain 'UAM:Herps:14' ; referring to both the specimen voucher and sampled tissue with the same identifier. However; the /culture_collection qualifier may refer to a value from an initial culture (e.g. ATCC:11775) while source_mat_id would refer to an identifier from some derived culture from which the nucleic acids were extracted (e.g. xatc123 or ark:/2154/R2).

name: specific_host
definition: If there is a host involved; please provide its taxid (or environmental if not actually isolated from the dead or alive host - i.e. pathogen could be isolated from a swipe of a bench etc) and report whether it is a laboratory or natural host). From this we can calculate any number of groupings of hosts (e.g. animal vs plant; all fish hosts; etc)

name: subspecf_gen_lin
definition: This should provide further information about the genetic distinctness of this lineage by recording additional information i.e biovar; serovar; serotype; biovar; or any relevant genetic typing schemes like Group I plasmid. It can also contain alternative taxonomic information

name: trophic_level
definition: Trophic levels are the feeding position in a food chain. Microbes can be a range of producers (e.g. chemolithotroph)

name: abs_air_humidity
definition: actual mass of water vapor - mh20 - present in the air water vapor mixture

name: agrochem_addition
definition: addition of fertilizers; pesticides; etc. - amount and time of applications

name: air_temp
definition: temperature of the air at the time of sampling

name: air_temp_regm
definition: information about treatment involving an exposure to varying temperatures; should include the temperature; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include different temperature regimens

name: al_sat
definition: aluminum saturation (esp. for tropical soils)

name: al_sat_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining Al saturation

name: alkalinity
definition: alkalinity; the ability of a solution to neutralize acids to the equivalence point of carbonate or bicarbonate

name: alkyl_diethers
definition: concentration of alkyl diethers

name: alt
definition: the altitude of the sample is the vertical distance between Earth's surface above sea level and the sampled position in the air

name: aminopept_act
definition: measurement of aminopeptidase activity

name: ammonium
definition: concentration of ammonium

name: amniotic_fluid_color
definition: specification of the color of the amniotic fluid sample

name: annual_season_precpt
definition: mean annual and seasonal precipitation

name: annual_season_temp
definition: mean annual and seasonal temperature

name: antibiotic_regm
definition: information about treatment involving antibiotic administration; should include the name of antibiotic; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple antibiotic regimens

name: atmospheric_data
definition: measurement of atmospheric data; can include multiple data

name: bac_prod
definition: bacterial production in the water column measured by isotope uptake

name: bac_resp
definition: measurement of bacterial resporation in the water column

name: bacteria_carb_prod
definition: measurement of bacterial carbon production

name: barometric_press
definition: force per unit area exerted against a surface by the weight of air above that surface

name: biochem_oxygen_dem
definition: a measure of the relative oxygen-depletion effect of a waste contaminant

name: biomass
definition: amount of biomass; should include the name for the part of biomass measured; e.g. microbial; total. can include multiple measurements

name: birth_control
definition: specification of birth control medication used

name: bishomohopanol
definition: concentration of bishomohopanol

name: blood_blood_disord
definition: history of blood disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: bromide
definition: concentration of bromide

name: build_occup_type
definition: the primary function for which a building or discrete part of a building is intended to be used

name: building_setting
definition: a location (geography) where a building is set

name: calcium
definition: concentration of calcium

name: carb_dioxide
definition: carbon dioxide (gas) amount or concentration at the time of sampling

name: carb_monoxide
definition: carbon monoxide (gas) amount or concentration at the time of sampling

name: carb_nitro_ratio
definition: ratio of amount or concentrations of carbon to nitrogen

name: chem_administration
definition: list of chemical compounds administered to the host or site where sampling occurred; and when (e.g. antibiotics; N fertilizer; air filter); can include multiple compounds. For Chemical Entities of Biological Interest ontology (CHEBI) (v 111); http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/CHEBI

name: chem_mutagen
definition: treatment involving use of mutagens; should include the name of mutagen; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple mutagen regimens

name: chem_oxygen_dem
definition: a measure of the relative oxygen-depletion effect of a waste contaminant

name: chloride
definition: concentration of chloride

name: chlorophyll
definition: concentration of chlorophyll

name: climate_environment
definition: treatment involving an exposure to a particular climate; can include multiple climates

name: conduc
definition: electrical conductivity of water

name: crop_rotation
definition: whether or not crop is rotated; and if yes; rotation schedule

name: cur_land_use
definition: present state of sample site

name: cur_vegetation
definition: vegetation classification from one or more standard classification systems; or agricultural crop

name: cur_vegetation_meth
definition: reference or method used in vegetation classification

name: dermatology_disord
definition: history of dermatology disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: dew_point
definition: the temperature to which a given parcel of humid air must be cooled; at constant barometric pressure; for water vapor to condense into water.

name: diet_last_six_month
definition: specification of major diet changes in the last six months; if yes the change should be specified

name: diether_lipids
definition: concentration of diether lipids; can include multiple types of diether lipids

name: diss_carb_dioxide
definition: concentration of dissolved carbon dioxide

name: diss_hydrogen
definition: concentration of dissolved hydrogen

name: diss_inorg_carb
definition: dissolved inorganic carbon concentration

name: diss_inorg_nitro
definition: concentration of dissolved inorganic nitrogen

name: diss_inorg_phosp
definition: concentration of dissolved inorganic phosphorus

name: diss_org_carb
definition: concentration of dissolved organic carbon

name: diss_org_nitro
definition: dissolved organic nitrogen concentration measured as; total dissolved nitrogen - NH4 - NO3 - NO2

name: diss_oxygen
definition: concentration of dissolved oxygen

name: dominant_hand
definition: dominant hand of the subject

name: douche
definition: date of most recent douche

name: down_par
definition: visible waveband radiance and irradiance measurements in the water column

name: drainage_class
definition: drainage classification from a standard system such as the USDA system

name: drug_usage
definition: any drug used by subject and the frequency of usage; can include multiple drugs used

name: efficiency_percent
definition: percentage of volatile solids removed from the anaerobic digestor

name: elev
definition: the elevation of the sampling site as measured by the vertical distance from mean sea level

name: emulsions
definition: amount or concentration of substances such as paints; adhesives; mayonnaise; hair colorants; emulsified oils; etc.; can include multiple emulsion types

name: extreme_event
definition: unusual physical events that may have affected microbial populations

name: extreme_salinity
definition: measured salinity

name: fao_class
definition: soil classification from the FAO World Reference Database for Soil Resources. The list can be found at http://www.fao.org/nr/land/sols/soil/wrb-soil-maps/reference-groups

name: fertilizer_regm
definition: information about treatment involving the use of fertilizers; should include the name fertilizer; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple fertilizer regimens

name: filter_type
definition: a device which removes solid particulates or airborne molecular contaminants

name: fire
definition: historical and/or physical evidence of fire

name: flooding
definition: historical and/or physical evidence of flooding

name: fluor
definition: raw or converted fluorescence of water

name: foetal_health_stat
definition: specification of foetal health status; should also include abortion

name: fungicide_regm
definition: information about treatment involving use of fungicides; should include the name of fungicide; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple fungicide regimens

name: gaseous_environment
definition: use of conditions with differing gaseous environments; should include the name of gaseous compound; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple gaseous environment regimens

name: gaseous_substances
definition: amount or concentration of substances such as hydrogen sulfide; carbon dioxide; methane; etc.; can include multiple substances

name: gastrointest_disord
definition: history of gastrointestinal tract disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: gestation_state
definition: specification of the gestation state

name: glucosidase_act
definition: measurement of glucosidase activity

name: gravidity
definition: whether or not subject is gravid; and if yes date due or date post-conception; specifying which is used

name: gravity
definition: information about treatment involving use of gravity factor to study various types of responses in presence; absence or modified levels of gravity; can include multiple treatments

name: growth_hormone_regm
definition: information about treatment involving use of growth hormones; should include the name of growth hormone; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple growth hormone regimens

name: growth_med
definition: information about growth media for growing the plants or tissue cultured samples

name: gynecologic_disord
definition: history of gynecological disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: heat_cool_type
definition: methods of conditioning or heating a room or building

name: heavy_metals
definition: heavy metals present and concentrationsany drug used by subject and the frequency of usage; can include multiple heavy metals and concentrations

name: heavy_metals_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining heavy metals

name: herbicide_regm
definition: information about treatment involving use of herbicides; information about treatment involving use of growth hormones; should include the name of herbicide; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple regimens

name: horizon
definition: specific layer in the land area which measures parallel to the soil surface and possesses physical characteristics which differ from the layers above and beneath

name: horizon_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining the horizon

name: host_age
definition: age of host at the time of sampling; relevant scale depends on species and study; e.g. could be seconds for amoebae or centuries for trees

name: host_blood_press_diast
definition: resting diastolic blood pressure; measured as mm mercury

name: host_blood_press_syst
definition: resting systolic blood pressure; measured as mm mercury

name: host_body_habitat
definition: original body habitat where the sample was obtained from

name: host_body_mass_index
definition: body mass index; calculated as weight/(height)squared

name: host_body_product
definition: substance produced by the body; e.g. stool; mucus; where the sample was obtained from. For Foundational Model of Anatomy Ontology (FMA) (v 3.1) terms; please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/FMA

name: host_body_site
definition: name of body site where the sample was obtained from

name: host_body_temp
definition: core body temperature of the host when sample was collected

name: host_color
definition: the color of host

name: host_common_name
definition: common name of the host; e.g. human

name: host_diet
definition: type of diet depending on the host; for animals omnivore; herbivore etc.; for humans high-fat; meditteranean etc.; can include multiple diet types

name: host_disease_stat
definition: list of diseases with which the host has been diagnosed; can include multiple diagnoses. the value of the field depends on host; for humans the terms should be chosen from DO (Disease Ontology) at http://www.disease-ontology.org; other hosts are free text

name: host_dry_mass
definition: measurement of dry mass

name: host_family_relationship
definition: relationships to other hosts in the same study; can include multiple relationships

name: host_genotype
definition: observed genotype

name: host_growth_cond
definition: literature reference giving growth conditions of the host

name: host_height
definition: the height of subject

name: host_hiv_stat
definition: HIV status of subject; if yes HAART initiation status should also be indicated as [YES or NO]

name: host_infra_specific_name
definition: taxonomic information about the host below subspecies level

name: host_infra_specific_rank
definition: taxonomic rank information about the host below subspecies level; such as variety; form; rank etc.

name: host_last_meal
definition: content of last meal and time since feeding; can include multiple values

name: host_length
definition: the length of subject

name: host_life_stage
definition: description of life stage of host

name: host_occupation
definition: most frequent job performed by subject

name: host_phenotype
definition: phenotype of host. For Phenotypic quality Ontology (PATO) (v 2013-10-28) terms; please see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/PATO

name: host_pulse
definition: resting pulse; measured as beats per minute

name: host_sex
definition: physical sex of the host

name: host_shape
definition: morphological shape of host

name: host_subject_id
definition: a unique identifier by which each subject can be referred to; de-identified; e.g. #131

name: host_substrate
definition: the growth substrate of the host

name: host_taxid
definition: NCBI taxon id of the host; e.g. 9606

name: host_tot_mass
definition: total mass of the host at collection; the unit depends on host

name: host_wet_mass
definition: measurement of wet mass

name: hrt
definition: whether subject had hormone replacement theraphy; and if yes start date

name: humidity
definition: amount of water vapour in the air; at the time of sampling

name: humidity_regm
definition: information about treatment involving an exposure to varying degree of humidity; information about treatment involving use of growth hormones; should include amount of humidity administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple regimens

name: hysterectomy
definition: specification of whether hysterectomy was performed

name: ihmc_ethnicity
definition: ethnicity of the subject

name: ihmc_medication_code
definition: can include multiple medication codes

name: indoor_space
definition: a distinguishable space within a structure; the purpose for which discrete areas of a building is used

name: indoor_surf
definition: type of indoor surface

name: indust_eff_percent
definition: percentage of industrial effluents received by wastewater treatment plant

name: inorg_particles
definition: concentration of particles such as sand; grit; metal particles; ceramics; etc.; can include multiple particles

name: kidney_disord
definition: history of kidney disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: light_intensity
definition: measurement of light intensity

name: light_type
definition: application of light to achieve some practical or aesthetic effect. Lighting includes the use of both artificial light sources such as lamps and light fixtures; as well as natural illumination by capturing daylight. Can also include absence of light

name: link_addit_analys
definition: link to additional analysis results performed on the sample

name: link_class_info
definition: link to digitized soil maps or other soil classification information

name: link_climate_info
definition: link to climate resource

name: liver_disord
definition: history of liver disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: local_class
definition: soil classification based on local soil classification system

name: local_class_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining the local soil classification

name: magnesium
definition: concentration of magnesium

name: maternal_health_stat
definition: specification of the maternal health status

name: mean_frict_vel
definition: measurement of mean friction velocity

name: mean_peak_frict_vel
definition: measurement of mean peak friction velocity

name: mechanical_damage
definition: information about any mechanical damage exerted on the plant; can include multiple damages and sites

name: medic_hist_perform
definition: whether full medical history was collected

name: menarche
definition: date of most recent menstruation

name: menopause
definition: date of onset of menopause

name: methane
definition: methane (gas) amount or concentration at the time of sampling

name: microbial_biomass
definition: the part of the organic matter in the soil that constitutes living microorganisms smaller than 5-10 micrometer. If you keep this; you would need to have correction factors used for conversion to the final units

name: microbial_biomass_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining microbial biomass

name: mineral_nutr_regm
definition: information about treatment involving the use of mineral supplements; should include the name of mineral nutrient; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple mineral nutrient regimens

name: misc_param
definition: any other measurement performed or parameter collected; that is not listed here

name: n_alkanes
definition: concentration of n-alkanes; can include multiple n-alkanes

name: nitrate
definition: concentration of nitrate

name: nitrite
definition: concentration of nitrite

name: nitro
definition: concentration of nitrogen (total)

name: non_mineral_nutr_regm
definition: information about treatment involving the exposure of plant to non-mineral nutrient such as oxygen; hydrogen or carbon; should include the name of non-mineral nutrient; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple non-mineral nutrient regimens

name: nose_mouth_teeth_throat_disord
definition: history of nose/mouth/teeth/throat disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: nose_throat_disord
definition: history of nose-throat disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: occup_samp
definition: number of occupants present at time of sample within the given space

name: occupant_dens_samp
definition: average number of occupants at time of sampling per square footage

name: org_carb
definition: concentration of organic carbon

name: org_matter
definition: concentration of organic matter

name: org_nitro
definition: concentration of organic nitrogen

name: org_particles
definition: concentration of particles such as faeces; hairs; food; vomit; paper fibers; plant material; humus; etc.

name: organism_count
definition: total count of any organism per gram or volume of sample; should include name of organism followed by count; can include multiple organism counts

name: oxy_stat_samp
definition: oxygenation status of sample

name: oxygen
definition: oxygen (gas) amount or concentration at the time of sampling

name: part_org_carb
definition: concentration of particulate organic carbon

name: part_org_nitro
definition: concentration of particulate organic nitrogen

name: particle_class
definition: particles are classified; based on their size; into six general categories:clay; silt; sand; gravel; cobbles; and boulders; should include amount of particle preceded by the name of the particle type; can include multiple values

name: perturbation
definition: type of perturbation; e.g. chemical administration; physical disturbance; etc.; coupled with time that perturbation occurred; can include multiple perturbation types

name: pesticide_regm
definition: information about treatment involving use of insecticides; should include the name of pesticide; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple pesticide regimens

name: pet_farm_animal
definition: specification of presence of pets or farm animals in the environment of subject; if yes the animals should be specified; can include multiple animals present

name: petroleum_hydrocarb
definition: concentration of petroleum hydrocarbon

name: ph
definition: pH measurement

name: ph_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining pH

name: ph_regm
definition: information about treatment involving exposure of plants to varying levels of pH of the growth media; can include multiple regimen

name: phaeopigments
definition: concentration of phaeopigments; can include multiple phaeopigments

name: phosphate
definition: concentration of phosphate

name: phosplipid_fatt_acid
definition: concentration of phospholipid fatty acids; can include multiple values

name: photon_flux
definition: measurement of photon flux

name: plant_body_site
definition: name of body site that the sample was obtained from. For Plant Ontology (PO) (v 20) terms; see http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/PO

name: plant_product
definition: substance produced by the plant; where the sample was obtained from

name: pollutants
definition: pollutant types and; amount or concentrations measured at the time of sampling; can report multiple pollutants by entering numeric values preceded by name of pollutant

name: pool_dna_extracts
definition: were multiple DNA extractions mixed? how many?

name: porosity
definition: porosity of deposited sediment is volume of voids divided by the total volume of sample

name: potassium
definition: concentration of potassium

name: pre_treatment
definition: the process of pre-treatment removes materials that can be easily collected from the raw wastewater

name: pregnancy
definition: date due of pregnancy

name: pressure
definition: pressure to which the sample is subject; in atmospheres

name: previous_land_use
definition: previous land use and dates

name: previous_land_use_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining previous land use and dates

name: primary_prod
definition: measurement of primary production

name: primary_treatment
definition: the process to produce both a generally homogeneous liquid capable of being treated biologically and a sludge that can be separately treated or processed

name: profile_position
definition: cross-sectional position in the hillslope where sample was collected.sample area position in relation to surrounding areas

name: pulmonary_disord
definition: history of pulmonary disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: radiation_regm
definition: information about treatment involving exposure of plant or a plant part to a particular radiation regimen; should include the radiation type; amount or intensity administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple radiation regimens

name: rainfall_regm
definition: information about treatment involving an exposure to a given amount of rainfall; can include multiple regimens

name: reactor_type
definition: anaerobic digesters can be designed and engineered to operate using a number of different process configurations; as batch or continuous; mesophilic; high solid or low solid; and single stage or multistage

name: redox_potential
definition: redox potential; measured relative to a hydrogen cell; indicating oxidation or reduction potential

name: rel_air_humidity
definition: partial vapor and air pressure; density of the vapor and air; or by the actual mass of the vapor and air

name: resp_part_matter
definition: concentration of substances that remain suspended in the air; and comprise mixtures of organic and inorganic substances (PM10 and PM2.5); can report multiple PM's by entering numeric values preceded by name of PM

name: salinity
definition: salinity measurement

name: salinity_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining salinity

name: salt_regm
definition: information about treatment involving use of salts as supplement to liquid and soil growth media; should include the name of salt; amount administered; treatment duration; interval and total experimental duration; can include multiple salt regimens

name: samp_salinity
definition: salinity of sample; i.e. measure of total salt concentration

name: samp_sort_meth
definition: method by which samples are sorted

name: samp_store_dur
definition: duration for which sample was stored

name: samp_store_loc
definition: location at which sample was stored; usually name of a specific freezer/room

name: samp_store_temp
definition: temperature at which sample was stored; e.g. -80 degree Celsius

name: samp_vol_we_dna_ext
definition: volume (mL) or weight (g) of sample processed for DNA extraction

name: season_environment
definition: treatment involving an exposure to a particular season (e.g. winter; summer; rabi; rainy etc.)

name: secondary_treatment
definition: the process for substantially degrading the biological content of the sewage

name: sediment_type
definition: information about the sediment type based on major constituents

name: sewage_type
definition: type of wastewater treatment plant as municipial or industrial

name: sexual_act
definition: current sexual partner and frequency of sex

name: sieving
definition: collection design of pooled samples and/or sieve size and amount of sample sieved

name: silicate
definition: concentration of silicate

name: slope_aspect
definition: the direction a slope faces. While looking down a slope use a compass to record the direction you are facing (direction or degrees); e.g.; NW or 315 degrees. This measure provides an indication of sun and wind exposure that will influence soil temperature and evapotranspiration.

name: slope_gradient
definition: commonly called 'slope'. The angle between ground surface and a horizontal line (in percent). This is the direction that overland water would flow. This measure is usually taken with a hand level meter or clinometer

name: sludge_retent_time
definition: the time activated sludge remains in reactor

name: smoker
definition: specification of smoking status

name: sodium
definition: sodium concentration

name: soil_type
definition: soil series name or other lower-level classification

name: soil_type_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining soil series name or other lower-level classification

name: solar_irradiance
definition: the amount of solar energy that arrives at a specific area of a surface during a specific time interval

name: soluble_inorg_mat
definition: concentration of substances such as ammonia; road-salt; sea-salt; cyanide; hydrogen sulfide; thiocyanates; thiosulfates; etc.

name: soluble_org_mat
definition: concentration of substances such as urea; fruit sugars; soluble proteins; drugs; pharmaceuticals; etc.

name: soluble_react_phosp
definition: concentration of soluble reactive phosphorus

name: space_typ_state
definition: customary or normal state of the space

name: special_diet
definition: specification of special diet; can include multiple special diets

name: standing_water_regm
definition: treatment involving an exposure to standing water during a plant's life span; types can be flood water or standing water; can include multiple regimens

name: store_cond
definition: explain how and for how long the soil sample was stored before DNA extraction.

name: study_complt_stat
definition: specification of study completion status; if no the reason should be specified

name: substructure_type
definition: the substructure or under building is that largely hidden section of the building which is built off the foundations to the ground floor level

name: sulfate
definition: concentration of sulfate

name: sulfide
definition: concentration of sulfide

name: surf_air_cont
definition: contaminant identified on surface

name: surf_humidity
definition: surfaces: water activity as a function of air and material moisture

name: surf_material
definition: surface materials at the point of sampling

name: surf_moisture
definition: water held on a surface

name: surf_moisture_ph
definition: pH measurement of surface

name: surf_temp
definition: temperature of the surface at the time of sampling

name: suspend_part_matter
definition: concentration of suspended particulate matter

name: suspend_solids
definition: concentration of substances including a wide variety of material; such as silt; decaying plant and animal matter; etc;; can include multiple substances

name: temp
definition: temperature of the sample at time of sampling

name: tertiary_treatment
definition: the process providing a final treatment stage to raise the effluent quality before it is discharged to the receiving environment

name: texture
definition: the relative proportion of different grain sizes of mineral particles in a soil; as described using a standard system; express as % sand (50 um to 2 mm); silt (2 um to 50 um); and clay (<2 um) with textural name (e.g.; silty clay loam) optional.

name: texture_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining soil texture

name: tidal_stage
definition: stage of tide

name: tillage
definition: note method(s) used for tilling

name: time_last_toothbrush
definition: specification of the time since last toothbrushing

name: time_since_last_wash
definition: specification of the time since last wash

name: tiss_cult_growth_med
definition: description of plant tissue culture growth media used

name: tot_carb
definition: total carbon content

name: tot_depth_water_col
definition: measurement of total depth of water column

name: tot_diss_nitro
definition: total dissolved nitrogen concentration; reported as nitrogen; measured by: total dissolved nitrogen = NH4 + NO3NO2 + dissolved organic nitrogen

name: tot_inorg_nitro
definition: total inorganic nitrogen content

name: tot_n_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining the total nitrogen

name: tot_nitro
definition: total nitrogen content of the sample

name: tot_org_c_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining total organic carbon

name: tot_org_carb
definition: Definition for soil: total organic carbon content of the soil; definition otherwise: total organic carbon content

name: tot_phosp
definition: total phosphorus concentration; calculated by: total phosphorus = total dissolved phosphorus + particulate phosphorus. Can also be measured without filtering; reported as phosphorus

name: tot_phosphate
definition: total amount or concentration of phosphate

name: travel_out_six_month
definition: specification of the countries travelled in the last six months; can include multiple travels

name: turbidity
definition: turbidity measurement

name: twin_sibling
definition: specification of twin sibling presence

name: typ_occupant_dens
definition: customary or normal density of occupants

name: urine_collect_meth
definition: specification of urine collection method

name: urogenit_disord
definition: history of urogenital disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: urogenit_tract_disor
definition: history of urogenitaltract disorders; can include multiple disorders

name: ventilation_rate
definition: ventilation rate of the system in the sampled premises

name: ventilation_type
definition: ventilation system used in the sampled premises

name: volatile_org_comp
definition: concentration of carbon-based chemicals that easily evaporate at room temperature; can report multiple volatile organic compounds by entering numeric values preceded by name of compound

name: wastewater_type
definition: the origin of wastewater such as human waste; rainfall; storm drains; etc.

name: water_content
definition: water content measurement

name: water_content_soil_meth
definition: reference or method used in determining the water content of soil

name: water_current
definition: measurement of magnitude and direction of flow within a fluid

name: water_temp_regm
definition: information about treatment involving an exposure to water with varying degree of temperature; can include multiple regimens

name: watering_regm
definition: information about treatment involving an exposure to watering frequencies; can include multiple regimens

name: weight_loss_3_month
definition: specification of weight loss in the last three months; if yes should be further specified to include amount of weight loss

name: wind_direction
definition: wind direction is the direction from which a wind originates

name: wind_speed
definition: speed of wind measured at the time of sampling

name: pcr_primers
definition: PCR primers that were used to amplify the sequence of the targeted gene; locus or subfragment. This field should contain all the primers used for a single PCR reaction if multiple forward or reverse primers are present in a single PCR reaction. The primer sequence should be reported in uppercase letters

name: seq_meth
definition: Sequencing method used; e.g. Sanger; pyrosequencing; ABI-solid

name: target_gene
definition: Targeted gene or locus name for marker gene studies

name: target_subfragment
definition: Name of subfragment of a gene or locus. Important to e.g. identify special regions on marker genes like V6 on 16S rRNA

name: adapters
definition: Adapters provide priming sequences for both amplification and sequencing of the sample-library fragments. Both adapters should be reported; in uppercase letters

name: annot_source
definition: For cases where annotation was provided by a community jamboree or model organism database rather than by a specific submitter

name: assembly
definition: How was the assembly done (e.g. with a text based assembler like phrap or a flowgram assembler); estimated error rate associated with the finished sequences (e.g. error rate of 1 in 1000 bp); and the method of calculation

name: assembly_name
definition: Name/version of the assembly provided by the submitter that is used in the genome browsers and in the community

name: chimera_check
definition: A chimeric sequence; or chimera for short; is a sequence comprised of two or more phylogenetically distinct parent sequences. Chimeras are usually PCR artifacts thought to occur when a prematurely terminated amplicon reanneals to a foreign DNA strand and is copied to completion in the following PCR cycles. The point at which the chimeric sequence changes from one parent to the next is called the breakpoint or conversion point

name: finishing_strategy
definition: Was the genome project intended to produce a complete or draft genome; Coverage; the fold coverage of the sequencing expressed as 2x; 3x; 18x  etc; and how many contigs were produced for the genome

name: lib_const_meth
definition: Library construction method used for clone libraries

name: lib_reads_seqd
definition: Total number of clones sequenced from the library

name: lib_screen
definition: Specific enrichment or screening methods applied before and/or after creating clone libraries

name: lib_size
definition: Total number of clones in the library prepared for the project

name: lib_vector
definition: Cloning vector type(s) used in construction of libraries

name: mid
definition: Molecular barcodes; called Multiplex Identifiers (MIDs); that are used to specifically tag unique samples in a sequencing run. Sequence should be reported in uppercase letters

name: nucl_acid_amp
definition: Link to a literature reference; electronic resource or a standard operating procedure (SOP)

name: nucl_acid_ext
definition: Link to a literature reference; electronic resource or a standard operating procedure (SOP)

name: pcr_cond
definition: Description of reaction conditions and components for PCR in the form of  'initial denaturation:94degC_1.5min; annealing=...'

name: seq_quality_check
definition: Indicate if the sequence has been called by automatic systems (none) or undergone a manual editing procedure (e.g. by inspecting the raw data or chromatograms). Applied only for sequences that are not submitted to SRA;ENA or DRA

name: sop
definition: Standard operating procedures used in assembly and/or annotation of genomes; metagenomes or environmental sequences

name: url
definition: relevant electronic resources
